5nrEG6lFlKfr-OluekbsTw
Maybe I ordered wrong but this was the blandest Thai food I've ever had. Mee krob was too sweet, tom ka gai was thin, and evil jungle princess was pretty one note. Ordered a 4 on a 5 point heat scale and could barely detect the spice. Added extra chile powder to try to zip up the flavor toward the end. That kind of helped, but not much. Every plate that I saw leave the kitchen appeared to be the same color! Service was okay, but there was only one person serving during the dinner rush. This place is adequate but not great.

