I can't believe I've never been here before. This will now be part of my routine when I travel to Chandler to stock up on supplies. Noodles had just the right amount of chew and were well seasoned. My favorite, though, was the spicy pig's ears: an old favorite that I haven't had in a long time. Lightly chewy and crispy at the same time, very thinly sliced, and nicely flavorful. Lunch and a show! Totally will be returning.

